  <title translate="true">TOP-TIPS</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">TOP-TIPS</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Interface2" translate="true">TOP-TIP #1</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">When you start using </text><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">MotionDesigner</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">, it is easy accidentally design a motion with a very short-segment that you cannot see in the graph, and that you do not know or want in your motion.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">To see if there is a very short </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">segment</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">, </text></para>
    <list id="0" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" translate="true">Open the Blend-Point Editor or the Segment Editor</text><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">&#32;</text></li>
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Click the </text><text styleclass="ParameterHeader" translate="true">Next</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> button, to move the </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Selected-Segment</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> across the complete motion. </text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">If the </text><text styleclass="Parameter" translate="true">Blend-Point number</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> increases by 1, but you cannot see the </text><text styleclass="Element" translate="true">Selected-Segment</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> in the motion graphs, then you have found a very short segment. </text></para>
    <list id="1" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="3" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" translate="true">Click the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Tools-DeleteSegment" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" translate="true">Delete Segment</link><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" translate="true"> button to remove the very short segment</text><text styleclass="VariableName" translate="true">&#32;</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Interface2" translate="true">TOP-TIP #2</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">On paper, plan you motion over one machine-cycle &#160;before you begin with MotionDesigner.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">From your plan, you should:</text></para>
    <list id="2" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Know if the motion is a progressive or non-progressive motion (indexing type, or Rise and Return type)</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Know how many segments you need in your motion - over a full machine cycle.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">Approximate the positions of each Blend-Point. </text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"></para>
  </body>
